minPost is a simple, minimal (and still in beta) CMS/blog for a website. It is writen in Perl, uses a MySQL database (info below) and the MooTools javascript framework to create a minimal interface with a few special effects.

Please edit the settings in settings.pl to fit your server setting.

MySQL database:
for the first release you will need only 2 tables in your database. Please edit the settings.pl page to fir your servers settings.

MySQL querys for the tables:

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `pl_content` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `date` date NOT NULL,
  `name` text NOT NULL,
  `post` text NOT NULL,
  KEY `id` (`id`)
) ENGINE=MyISAM DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;


CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `pl_db` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `date` date NOT NULL,
  `name` text NOT NULL,
  `email` text NOT NULL,
  `post` text NOT NULL,
  KEY `date` (`date`)
) ENGINE=MyISAM DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;
